My baby before I had a baby = still my baby 🥹❤️‍🩹

We’ve been going through it with our Dexter boy if you’ve been watching my stories. We are now onto his fourth surgery. And this video was actually after his third, which was hard enough for the entire family but after this video, we really thought it was it. It’s crazy to think that by the time I posted this video that he had to have another surgery after he was finally rehabilitated.

His story summed up: he tore his ACL and our vet messed up the surgery. His recovery was so bad and we kept addressing this concern to our vet in which he kept making excuses: he’s itching his leg which is causing him to be unable to walk, it’s going to get worse before it gets better, it’s going to take time. But in our mom and dad hearts, we knew. 

The vet suggested he was having an allergic reaction to the plate and screws so we went through with another surgery to get those removed.

He tore his second ACL in his other leg, which left him unable to walk or move. If the surgery had worked, he wouldn’t be unable to move or walk on the surgery leg. It was just ridiculous. And because it was never done right and then it never healed right, he then tore the other leg because it was doing all of the work and rehabilitation. And honestly, it was even worse than leaving an ACL untreated because for a TPLO surgery you cut the bone and you create a new angle since there is now no ACL. Well, that angle was done wrong so imagine your bone not aligned how it should be. That would be such an uncomfortable and painful feeling, far worse than an untreated ACL tear that would just get stronger overtime.

We then took the x-ray results to a new vet. Who was not a board certified surgeon, but he was a specialist in this specific surgery. He took one quick look and did a measurement and the angle of the bone was extremely wrong. He immediately suggested double leg surgery. Seriously our worst nightmare. We felt so bad for our dog.
Date nights, date days, and my cute lil fam 🤍
